rComments: I liked Professor Rahr's teaching style. She was very patient and engaging. Readings were interesting - crucial to the classes and exam. Participation makes up a large portion of your mark. Overall a great prof, the only criticism I have is that going into the exam we only had 25% of our mark, so we really did not have an idea of our performance.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Prof Rahr is great, she gives excellent lectures and provides the class a lot of opportunity to ask questions and give their opinion on whatever topic is being discussed. She isn't a fan of you coming in late or leaving during the lecture, and you really need to be in class every week, your lecture notes will be super important for the exam.

Never took American studies before, but really interesting and captivating. Intellectually I was very exhausted by the end of it because I'd learnt so much. The assignments are fair. Very heavy on participation and she actually marks if you speak in class or attend. Pretty impossible to go on your phone, which was a good thing for my attention span
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I had never taken an American Studies class before, but Prof Rahr really helped me figure out what it was all about. She gave me lots of advice about assignments which helped me better understand what I could do with the material. She cares so much about her students and really makes an effort to individuate them. Also she is a walking dictionary

I went in not really knowing what to expect and ended up having a great time! I definitely wouldn't have enjoyed it so much if it weren't for Dr Rahr. I found some of the assignments a little tricky (I'm in the sciences) but she gave a lot f helpful feedback and I def got better by the end!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: shes a really nice individual and a cool prof! made me feel a lot better about uoft
I went into the class not really knowing what to expect and came out loving American studies!! She's so nice and made me feel listened to
This course was tough, but Dr. Rahr helped me understand all the dense theory so well! I really appreciated how helpful and approachable she was outside of class
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Inspirational', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Best prof at UofT - she makes an effort to know each and every student, and makes every lecture inspiring
I want to take every course she has to offer! No other professor has compared to Prof Rahr!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Professor Rahr is a gem at UofT. It's so rare for a prof to care so much about the success of her students. She's always willing to help out, and gives constructive feedback
Great prof! She's great at generating enthusiasm and helps hone research and writing skills

Prof. Rahr gave amazing lectures! This course was so engaging and I learned a lot. As a first year student, I found it to be a pretty difficult course. However, Prof. Rahr was so passionate about the material and helping her students. Lots of discussions in this class and she loves people who raise their hands and have something to add.

Prof Rahr is an outstanding lecturer, very approachable, and provides useful feedback. She's great at encouraging students to think from all different perspectives and loves eagerness. Take an American Studies course just to be her student.
You won't skip class with Prof Rahr
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Caring', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Most underrated prof at UofT - immensely knowledgeable with an unparalled kindness.
An inspirational prof who works hard to give her students the best experience they can receive.

Prof Rahr is incredible. Not only is her intellect dazzling, but she is extremely approachable and always goes above and beyond for her students. She explains concepts clearly, and her lectures facilitate rich discussions.

This was my first class in the field and I am so glad to have such a great prof. Her teaching style is an actual lecture with powerpoint as a medium for pictures so I would not suggest skipping class. Professor Rahr engages us well and synthesizes material taught before as well as current day scenarios to new material. Her fashion is also on point.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Graded by few things', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I found USA200 to be more like a poetry class. We analyzed poems/writings from the 1800's FOREVER in every detail. For the assignment and paper, we were to analyze a new poem, from the perspective of the former poem. I thought it was terrible. Prof Rahr is very knowledgeable, passionate and well spoken. If you are into this style you will love it.

I had her for USA200 and I found her lectures very hard to follow. She spoke a lot in metaphors, which was difficult to understand. She often started discussions and didn't finish them, leaving out the key points. I did not enjoy this class because of her difficult-to-follow lectures.

Try and take a course with her early on in your English major as she really helps you figure out how to participate well in class and write strong papers. She is well prepared for every class and places each text carefully in its historical, political and literary context. Best class I took at U of T.

Professor Rahr is a fantastic professor.  Her lectures are very interesting and easy to follow.  She makes them very interesting with providing historical context around the texts you read. Would definitely recommend taking her courses!

Where do I even begin. I wish she taught every English course ugh. She's super clear, very articulate and knows her stuff inside out. I love that she would talk about the art, culture, music & history of the time period of the book we were discussing. Grading was very fair and you'd do great on the test if you went to lecture.

By far the best English TA any student can have. The skills you will learn, based on the feedback on your essays, will make you a better write in all your classes. She is a fair marker, and always available to answer questions. Take the time to see her and you will become a better writer!
Best TA ever!
brilliant TA. Very knowledgeable and always willing to help. She makes you a better writer by writing detailed comments on your assignments.
Best TA ever! Super helpful and welcoming... Makes the class even better, if that's possible.
